description: 1975 Ericson 23-II Sailboat. This is the  model with the shoal draft keel and centerboard which enhances it's gunkholing abilities and trailerability. The double axle Trail-Rite trailer for this boat is included. Also includes: 9 bags of Hood sails (original), 6 Barlow winches, spinnaker gear, reaching strut, boat hook, Evenrude 7.5 hp outboard, a brand new Standard Horizon VHF radio, all standing and running rigging, anchor and ground tackle, porta-potti, misc. gear, life jackets, spares, etc. It is a complete, trailerable sailing vessel that is rigged for single or shorthanded sailing and can sleep four. A very solid boat, that is is being sold "as is". Some TLC would be appropriate. In 2007 an epoxy barrier coat replaced the gel coat below the water line and new bottom paint was last done in 2012. This is a great sailing boat and has served me and my family well for many years on Southern Oregon lakes as well as numerous trips to the San Juan Islands and the lower Columbia River from Astoria to Bonneville. The boat is currently located in Ashland on the trailer. Delivery is negotiable. Centerboard repair or replacement MAY need to occur within the next few seasons. If so, I have the patterns and dimensions, and the plug used for making the fiberglass mold when the stock centerboard was replaced in 1997 (see photo). ALL REASONABLE OFFERS WILL BE CONSIDERED.
